@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Easy installation: just run the game and play!

-You can choose the size of the labyrinth. Any size between an  area
 of 11 by 11 tiles up to an area of 59 by 59 tiles can be choosen.

-ezaMaze is a "Workbench" game, so it's meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will be automatically
 resized to the smallest displayable size.

-You can play the game with the mouse or with the cursor keys of the
 keyboard.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-ezaMaze works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first version
of this game.

1.0: -First release.

1.1: -The moving routine has been changed: Now you can click in the
      direction you want to move, not just on the space immediately next
      to your position.
     -Some other minor changes were made to the game code.

2.0: -Bugfix: When the 'About' window was displayed and it overlapped the
      game board, the player could click on the tiles 'through' the About
      window.
     -Now the size of the labyrinth can be choosen.
     -Many changes have been made to the program code:
       -The game display routine has been enhanced.
       -The routine that generates the game window has been revised.
       -The 'progress bar' routine has been revised and it is now shown in
        the game window.
       -Lots of other internal changes.

2.01: -Bugfix: When choosing a labyrinth size, that size could exceed the
       maximum size allowed by the game.
      -When choosing a labyrinth size, if you click at a position that is
       smaller, either in width and/or height, than the minimum labyrinth
       size, the black rectangle that indicates the labyrinth size will be
       drawn to its minimum width and/or height.
      -Various other small changes have been made to the program code.

2.1: -Now you can move by clicking in the general direction you want to
      move instead of in line, horizontally or vertically, from your
      actual position.
     -Now the game window can be resized up to a maximum of 640 x 400
      pixels.
     -When you complete the game and the number of moves exceed 9999 (!),
      the game shows the word "many" instead of the actual number of
      moves.
     -The "progress bar" routine has been revised.
     -The game board display routine has been revised.
     -The routine that checks if the game window is too small has been
      revised.
     -Various other changes have been made to the program code.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "ezaMaze" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. 

                             How to play?

  Your position is indicated by the smiling face icon in the center of
the display. To play, click on a space in the general direction you
want to move. If the move is possible (no walls blocking in the choosen
direction) the display is then updated at the new position. Note that
you can also use the cursor keys to move in the maze.

  The exit tile is marked by an "E" (or "Exit") and is always located
in a dead end. If you get on that tile, the game ends and displays how
many moves it took to get there, then ezaMaze creates a new maze to
explore...

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button
(or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

LABYRINTH SIZE

  To change the labyrinth size, click on the "Game size" button, this
will clear the main window and display a large area with a black
rectangle, the upper left of the rectangle will always be at the
upper left of the large area. Click in the area and a new black
rectangle will appear with its lower right edge at the position you
clicked on. On the upper right in the window, a "Board size" text
displays the area of that black rectangle which is the size of the
labyrinth you are choosing. Note that you can also use the cursor
keys to enlarge or reduce the labyrinth size.

  When you have choosen a labyrinth size you like, click on the "use"
button and the game will return to 'play mode' where you will be able
to play with a labyrinth of that size.

  However, if you want to keep the initial labyrinth size either
click on the "cancel" button or the window's closebutton and the game
will return to the displayed labyrinth.

  Have fun!

@endnode

